@node Export Templates
@section Export Templates
@abstract{How to use export templates.}

@cindex export templates

Templates allow you to export your database to a large variety of formats. It also allows you to 
customize to a great extent how the data is exported.

To export using templates, choose the @menutitle{Export@dots{}} menu item, which can be found 
under the @menutitle{File} menu. You can choose the template from the @buttontitle{File Format} 
popup button. You can either export the whole database, or just the references which you have selected. 

BibDesk provides several default templates, for export to HTML, RSS, Rich Text (RTF, RTFD) and to windows Doc format. 

In order to use a non-default template the last menu item @menutitle{Using Template} should be chosen. 
This allows you to choose a template from a popup button in the save dialog window. 

