@node Script Hooks
@section Script Hooks
@abstract{How to use Script Hooks.}

@cindex script hooks

Sometimes you want to perform a particular AppleScript every time a certain action occurs. 
For example, you might want to have field that depends in a definite way on some other fields, 
so it can be handy if Bibdesk would auto generate this field for you. This is already built in 
for the Local-Url field and the Cite Key, but what about other fields?  As another example, 
you might want to commit a file linked by the Local-Url field to cvs or subversion 
whenever the file is moved by Auto File. 

For such times, BibDesk allows you to add custom AppleScripts that are automatically run 
when certain events occur. These are called Script Hooks in BibDesk. 

You can add Script Hooks in the preferences, see the @ref{Script Hook Preferences} 
preference guide for how to do this. The preferences also list the names of the 
various script hooks that BibDesk recognizes.

Go to the item linked below to see a sample script. 

